{
  "texts": [
    "This indicates a need for more reliable evidence on this research topic (Tang et al., 2020).",
    "For instance, scholars like De Araujo et al. and Lockwood and Mooney, and Moreno-Leon et al.",
    "have all concluded that CT is composed of various skills, but programming is the most commonly used method, and programming and multiplechoice questionnaires are the most commonly used tools for evaluating CT capabilities (Araujo et al., 2016; Lockwood & Mooney, 2017; Moreno-Leon et al., 2018).",
    "Against this backdrop, we decided to mainly refer to the theoretical framework of computational thinking proposed by the International Society for Technology in Education (ISTE) to conduct an inductive analysis of the computational thinking evaluation dimensions of various related literature (ISTE, 2023).",
    "It's worth noting that scholars like Özgen Korkmaz and Zhang Yi adopted the same framework when creating their CT scales (Korkmaz et al., 2017; Su et al., 2022; Ding et al., 2020)."
  ]
}